  "description": "Raising alpacas (Vicugna pacos) and llamas (Lama glama) for fiber, pack transport, and guard duty. Alpacas produce 2-5 kg of fine fiber every 12-18 months; llamas carry 25-30% of body weight as pack animals and serve as livestock guardians against predators. Both are hardy, disease-resistant, and use communal dung piles for easy manure collection.",
